# Server Administration: A Simple Guide

This documentation provides a straightforward guide to installing and configuring essential Windows Server roles and features for managing users and computers within a network environment.

Prerequisites

Before proceeding with the installation and configuration steps, ensure your host machine meets the following minimum requirements:

Processor: 1.4 GHz 64-bit processor
Memory: 2 GB RAM (4 GB recommended for optimal performance)
Storage 32 GB of storage space
Network Ethernet Adapter of 1GBps






   



